programme.desc: Shakespeare's play about a collection of people who have a mystical, comedic and humorous experience in the forest, where their romantic entanglements are resolved through the mischief of the fairies.

programme.title: The Tall Target
programme.desc: A police detective uncovers a sinister plot to assassinate President Lincoln during a train ride, and must furiously work against time to prevent it.

programme.title: Murder, My Sweet
programme.desc: Adaptation of Raymond Chandler's "Farewell, My Lovely" puts hard-boiled private eye Philip Marlowe in the middle of a case involving blackmail and murder when he's hired by a hulking psychotic to find his missing girlfriend. Movie crooner Dick Powell is cast against type as Marlowe. The story was first filmed in 1942 (as "The Falcon Takes Over," with George Sanders), then was remade (as "Farewell, My Lovely," with Robert Mitchum) in 1975.

programme.title: The Bad and the Beautiful
programme.desc: Tinseltown takes a pounding in this portrait of a classic Hollywood heel, a callous, cutthroat producer who seduces and schemes his way to the top. Oscars went to Charles Schnee (Screenplay) and Gloria Grahame (Supporting Actress), and Kirk Douglas, as the producer, was nominated for Best Actor.

programme.title: Touch of Evil
programme.desc: Orson Welles directed and stars in this stylish thriller about a corrupt detective in a Mexican border town. Charlton Heston, Janet Leigh, Marlene Dietrich, Joseph Calleia, Akim Tamiroff, Joanna Moore, Zsa Zsa Gabor. Score by Henry Mancini.

programme.title: The Player
programme.desc: A studio executive in crisis is getting death threats; wants to dump his girlfriend; and senses another exec is angling for his job.

programme.title: Pillow Talk
programme.desc: Rock Hudson-Doris Day romp about a playboy songwriter and a career woman who feud over their shared party line, then meet and fall in love. An Oscar winner for Best Original Screenplay; Day was nominated for Best Actress; and Thelma Ritter received a Best Supporting Actress nod as Day's tipsy maid.

programme.title: Who's That Girl?
programme.desc: A lawyer engagned to a snob gets involved in a wacky adventure with a free-spirited ex-con and begins to question his decision to marry.

programme.desc: Four would-be Lotharios go in together on an apartment---which, in turn, is sublet by an ersatz call girl, who is really a doctoral candidate working on her thesis: "Adolescent Sexual Fantasies in the Adult Suburban Male."

programme.title: Chances

programme.title: Little Women
